# Frontend build-time env vars (Vite). Copy to `.env.local` for local dev.
#
# All are OPTIONAL. With NONE set, the site runs a **prompt-aware in-browser
# simulation**: it reads your prompt, infers the domain, and generates on-topic
# hypotheses locally (nothing leaves the device). For a live model's *reasoning*,
# bake in one credential below.

# ── Live reasoning (recommended): a free Groq key ────────────────────────────
# https://console.groq.com/keys — when set, every session calls Groq to generate
# genuinely prompt-specific hypotheses. Browsers can't call Groq anonymously, so
# the key is bundled into the static site and is publicly visible: use a FREE,
# rotatable key you can revoke, never a paid one.
# VITE_GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...

# ── Optional keyless-style provider: Pollinations ────────────────────────────
# Pollinations gates browser-origin requests behind a Turnstile bot-check unless
# the request carries a REGISTERED token/referrer. Register a referrer at
# https://pollinations.ai and set the token here to enable it (otherwise the app
# skips it and uses the local simulation).
# VITE_POLLINATIONS_TOKEN=...

# ── Static-demo / hosted-backend wiring (usually only set in CI) ─────────────
# VITE_STATIC_DEMO=true          # build the no-backend static site
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com   # point at a hosted co_scientist backend
